{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"06267280-3f12-4698-8971-678f03f0b753","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin to the .NET 11 SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then rebuild and test:**\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\ndotnet test   # if you have tests\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages targeting `net10.0` — you may need updated versions that support `net11.0`. Run `dotnet list package --outdated` to find them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"33b6ad6c-629d-47b6-b12c-55efa950f2a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":294,"requestId":"983B:12A78D:229C1A:2B6596:69F5562F"},"id":"0e058957-d876-4931-8028-afc00d2db4f6","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:41:10.355Z","parentId":"9aa66a49-9567-4ced-987f-032fd9463248"}
